cardio1 = Workout("1 mile run", "cardio", "both", 65, "Running a mile is a great way to improve overall fitness and health. There are many benefits to incorporating a mile run into your regular exercise routine, including physical, mental, and emotional benefits. Here are some of the top benefits of running a mile: Improved cardiovascular health: Running a mile is an excellent way to improve your heart health. Regular running helps to lower your blood pressure, improve your cholesterol levels, and reduce your risk of heart disease. Increased endurance and stamina: Running a mile regularly can improve your overall fitness and increase your endurance and stamina. It helps your body to become more efficient at using oxygen, which can help you to run longer distances with less fatigue. Weight loss and management: Running a mile is a great way to burn calories and lose weight. It is a high-intensity exercise that can help you to burn more calories in less time than many other forms of exercise. Additionally, running regularly can help you to maintain a healthy weight.", "data:image/jpeg;base64,")

upperbody1 = Workout("Pull-ups", "upper body", "male", 50, "Pull-ups are a highly effective exercise for strengthening the upper body, particularly the back, shoulders, and arms. They can be done with minimal equipment and are easily scalable, making them a great option for people of all fitness levels. Pull-ups work multiple muscle groups at once, helping to improve overall muscle strength and tone. They also help to improve grip strength, which can be beneficial for many everyday activities. Pull-ups are also a compound exercise, meaning they work multiple joints and muscles simultaneously, leading to greater overall calorie burn and improved metabolic rate. In summary, pull-ups are a versatile and efficient exercise that can provide numerous benefits for overall health and fitness.", "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1497/9682/files/2_434b8599-da71-4153-9ee8-ba74a7b36626.jpg?v=1648821574")
db_session.add(upperbody1)


upperbody2 = Workout("Bench press", "upper body", "male", 50, "Until failure. The bench press is a popular exercise for building upper body strength, particularly in the chest, shoulders, and triceps. It can also engage the back muscles and core, making it a compound exercise that works multiple muscle groups at once. Consistently performing bench press can lead to increased muscle mass, improved overall strength, and enhanced upper body power. Additionally, the bench press can help to improve bone density, joint stability, and posture. It is also a scalable exercise, meaning that it can be modified to suit a variety of fitness levels and goals. Overall, incorporating the bench press into your workout routine can provide numerous benefits for upper body strength, stability, and overall health.", "https://image.boxrox.com/2022/02/Athlete-Incline-Bench-Press.png")
db_session.add(upperbody2)

upperbody3 = Workout("Bicep curls", "upper body", "female", 50, "4 sets of 10, 10-20 lbs depending on proficiency. Bicep curls are an isolation exercise that primarily work the muscles in the front of the upper arm. They can be done with a variety of equipment, including dumbbells, barbells, or resistance bands, making them a versatile exercise that can be done anywhere. Bicep curls are effective for building strength and muscle mass in the biceps, which can help to improve overall arm strength and functionality. Additionally, regularly performing bicep curls can improve grip strength, which can be beneficial for many everyday activities. Bicep curls are also a scalable exercise, meaning they can be modified to suit a variety of fitness levels and goals. In summary, incorporating bicep curls into your workout routine can provide numerous benefits for overall upper body strength and functionality, making it a highly effective exercise for improving overall fitness and health.", "https://experiencelife.lifetime.life/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/f2-biceps-curl.jpg")
db_session.add(upperbody3)

lowerbody1 = Workout("Squat", "lower body", "both", 50, "4 sets of 20, add weight as desired. Squats are a fundamental exercise that can provide numerous benefits for overall strength, balance, and mobility. They work the muscles in the legs, including the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes, as well as the lower back and core muscles. Regularly performing squats can help to build lower body strength, improve balance and stability, and increase overall flexibility and mobility. Additionally, squatting can improve bone density, which can be beneficial for preventing osteoporosis and other age-related conditions. Squats are also a scalable exercise, meaning they can be modified to suit a variety of fitness levels and goals. In summary, incorporating squats into your workout routine can provide numerous benefits for overall lower body strength, balance, and mobility, making it a highly effective exercise for improving overall fitness and health.", "https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/squat-jump-squat-178-1653334247.jpg?crop=0.859xw:0.646xh;0.0481xw,0.342xh&resize=1200:*")
db_session.add(lowerbody1)

core1 = Workout("Sit-ups", "core", "both", 50, "4 sets of 20. Sit-ups are a popular exercise for strengthening the abdominal muscles. They are a bodyweight exercise that can be done without any equipment, making them a convenient and accessible exercise option. Regularly performing sit-ups can help to build core strength, which can improve overall posture and stability. Additionally, a strong core can help to reduce the risk of injury during other exercises and everyday activities. Sit-ups can also improve overall flexibility and mobility in the spine, which can lead to better overall health and wellness. However, it is important to note that sit-ups can put stress on the neck and back if done incorrectly, so it is important to use proper form and consult a professional if you are new to the exercise. In summary, incorporating sit-ups into your workout routine can provide numerous benefits for core strength and overall health, making them a simple yet effective exercise for improving overall fitness.", "https://www.spotebi.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/sit-up-exercise-illustration.jpg")
db_session.add(core1)

db_session.commit()


